<br>
********************* <br>
<br>
I like many of the discussions/views here. And at the very least, most are civil [to an extent] to each other.<br>
<br>
Here's my situation:<br>
<br>
My Account:<br>
60 Warrior<br>
57 Cleric<br>
<br>
Other Account:<br>
60 Cleric<br>
50 Druid<br>
<br>
Are we thrilled? You bet.<br>
<br>
Are we worried? Definitely.<br>
<br>
In Raid situations, the roles will continue to be the way they are right now. Warriors MT, Clerics CH. Unlikely that this would change. We LOVE this change cos it only serves to make the Raids more efficient. Even we Clerics can be hard-pressed at times to heal [ever seen the piles and piles of R2 that we eat? hehe. talk about gluttony!]. So any form of improved healing on a Raid-level is always welcome!  <br>
<br>
In non-Raid situations, these roles then begin to blur. Yes, at the moment, Clerics are pretty much welcome in XP-groups. But here's the catch:<br>
<br>
Druid enters zone.<br>
Druid shouts,'55 Druid LFG'<br>
&lt;...silence...&gt;<br>
Druid shouts,'55 Druid LFG'<br>
&lt;...cricket sounds...&gt;<br>
Druid tells himself,'Hmmph, no group. Oh well, guess I'll go quad something, or maybe root-rot something.'<br>
<br>
Cleric enters zone.<br>
Cleric shouts,'55 Cleric LFG'<br>
&lt;...silence...&gt;<br>
Cleric shouts,'55 Cleric LFG'<br>
&lt;...cricket sounds...&gt;<br>
Cleric tells himself,'Dang, no group. Sh!t. Now what? Hmm, guess I'll have to wait for an opening then. Can't solo these things for nuts anyway,'<br>
Cleric shouts,'55 Cleric LFG. PST!!'<br>
<br>
The above is what gets us worried. Druids do not have it as easy as us Clerics in finding groups, but in the event that a group is not available, a Druid can still effectively [STRESS EFFECTIVELY] solo his way through most mobs.<br>
<br>
Clerics who are unable to find a spot in a group MIGHT be able to solo, but at a very INEFFICIENT rate.<br>
<br>
<br>
Do any of you still remember the life of a Druid from levels 15 - 34 back in the old days? [No, Plevel Twinks need not apply here].<br>
Remember how Druids were more desired over Clerics cos the healing was almost similar, but Druids could do more?<br>
Remember how Clerics became more desirable after L34, when we got Superior Healing?<br>
<br>
This may not be an exact example, but the similarities are there to see. Prior to L54, Clerics may be more desirable in groups, but post-L54, Druids may very well become the main choice in groups over Clerics.<br>
<br>
So unless Verant can supply Clerics with the options of EFFECTIVELY solo'ing in the advent of a non-group availability, Clerics will continue to view this change with trepediation and angst.<br>
<br>
Cheers!  <br>
<br>
**<br>
<br>
Again this isn't my outlook, being a 56 Druid I HOPE this goes through, but does make for interesting discussion.  Didn't clerics get upset/petition like mad when paly's got Rez ablility? If I am playing a alt looking for a healer, we will for sure go with cleric due to HP buffs and Rez, can't replace that.  Unless Shammy and Paly in the group as well oh well we will just wait and see what happens /shrug<br>
<br>
Kilase<br>
56 Preserver <br>
